\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Method overview and empirical results.} \textbf  {(A)} The proposed 3-stage pipeline: an encoder with self-attention (Stage~1) feeds a recurrent memory module (Stage~2) that supplies context to a skill-conditioned decoder (Stage~3), with a residual skip connection from Stage~1 to Stage~3 and an attention-feedback loop from Stage~2 to Stage~1. \textbf  {(B)} Ablation study: removing any single component (attention~$-$attn, memory~$-$mem, residual~$-$residual, or skill decoder~$-$skill) degrades accuracy relative to the full model (64.7\,\%), with the memory module contributing the largest gain ($\Delta {=}9.6$\,pp). \textbf  {(C)} Training-loss curves over 30k steps showing that our method converges faster and to a lower final loss than the baseline. \textbf  {(D)} Sensitivity sweep across a $5{\times }5$ grid of hyperparameters $\{S_0$--$S_4\}{\times }\{P_0$--$P_4\}$; scores in $[0,1]$, higher is better.}}{1}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:overview}{{1}{1}{\textbf {Method overview and empirical results.} \textbf {(A)} The proposed 3-stage pipeline: an encoder with self-attention (Stage~1) feeds a recurrent memory module (Stage~2) that supplies context to a skill-conditioned decoder (Stage~3), with a residual skip connection from Stage~1 to Stage~3 and an attention-feedback loop from Stage~2 to Stage~1. \textbf {(B)} Ablation study: removing any single component (attention~$-$attn, memory~$-$mem, residual~$-$residual, or skill decoder~$-$skill) degrades accuracy relative to the full model (64.7\,\%), with the memory module contributing the largest gain ($\Delta {=}9.6$\,pp). \textbf {(C)} Training-loss curves over 30k steps showing that our method converges faster and to a lower final loss than the baseline. \textbf {(D)} Sensitivity sweep across a $5{\times }5$ grid of hyperparameters $\{S_0$--$S_4\}{\times }\{P_0$--$P_4\}$; scores in $[0,1]$, higher is better}{figure.1}{}}
