\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Accuracy (\%) of four methods across five benchmarks (MMLU, HumanEval, GSM8K, MATH, GPQA). Error bars show sample standard deviation over 5 random seeds. \textbf  {RetroDiff} (green, cross-hatch) achieves the highest accuracy on every benchmark, with an average gain of $\mathbf  {+6.4}$\,pp over the strongest baseline (Method-B). Data are synthetic but follow realistic distributions; see \texttt  {data.json}.}}{2}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:benchmarks}{{2}{2}{Accuracy (\%) of four methods across five benchmarks (MMLU, HumanEval, GSM8K, MATH, GPQA). Error bars show sample standard deviation over 5 random seeds. \textbf {\methodname } (green, cross-hatch) achieves the highest accuracy on every benchmark, with an average gain of $\mathbf {+6.4}$\,pp over the strongest baseline (Method-B). Data are synthetic but follow realistic distributions; see \texttt {data.json}}{figure.2}{}}
